"Miholcsa T., Tóth A., Csörgo T.","Change of timing of autumn migration in acrocephalus and locustella genus",2009,"Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae","55","2",,"175","185",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-70349206176&partnerID=40&md5=fa845e608b34945d6436af0f3fb7513a","Eötvös Loránd University, Department General Biology, Pázmány sétány 1/C, 1117 Budapest, Hungary","Miholcsa, T., Eötvös Loránd University, Department General Biology, Pázmány sétány 1/C, 1117 Budapest, Hungary; Tóth, A., Eötvös Loránd University, Department General Biology, Pázmány sétány 1/C, 1117 Budapest, Hungary; Csörgo, T., Eötvös Loránd University, Department General Biology, Pázmány sétány 1/C, 1117 Budapest, Hungary","Our research was done on trans-Sahara migrant Acrocephalus and Locustella species caught in Ócsa (Hungary) with standardized conditions between 1987-2004. We have constructed the cumulative diagram of the migration for adults and juveniles for every year and we have established the dates of the 50 and 90% percentiles. We have represented these data in the function of years and the average temperatures of August. On these distributions we have made linear regressions and studied their parameters. The very close related species react to the climate change in different degrees and direction. Although the study period is short, we have found some significant changes in the timing of migration and correlations with the temperature. The early migrating species have advanced their autumn migration and the later-migrating species have delayed it. The migration strategies of the species are very complex, so it is hard to give a uniform explanation for the changes.","Bird; Climate change; Global warming; Long-distance migrant; Migration; Trans-sahara migrant","Acrocephalus; Aves; Locustella",,,,,,"Bergmann, F., Langfristige Zunahme früher Bruten beim Teichrohrsänger (Acrocephalus scirpaceus) in einem südwestdeutschen Untersuchungsgebiet (1999) Journal of Ornithology, 140, pp. 81-86; Berthold, P., Evolutionary aspects of migratory behaviour in European warblers (1988) Journal of Evolutionary Biology, 1, pp. 195-209; Berthold, P., (1994) Bird migration, a general survey, p. 239. , Oxford Ornithology Series, Oxford University Press, Oxford; Berthold, P., (1996) Control of bird migration, p. 355. , Chapman & Hall, London; Berthold, P., Querner, U., Genetic basis of migratory behavior in European warblers (1981) Science, 212, pp. 77-79; Bezzel, E., Jetz, W., Verschiebung der Wegzugperiode bei der Mönchsgrasmücke (Sylvia atricapilla) 1966-1993 - Reaktion auf die Klimaerwärmung? (1995) Journal of Ornithology, 136, pp. 83-87; Both, C., Visser, M.E., Adjustment to climate change is constrained by arrival date in a long-distance migrant bird (2001) Nature, 411, pp. 296-298; Both, C., Artemeyev, A.V., Blaauw, B., Cowie, R.J., Dekhuijzen, A.J., Eeva, T., Enemar, A., Visser, M.E., Large-scale geographical variation confirms that climate change causes bird to lay earlier (2004) Proceedings of the Royal Society, London, B, 271, pp. 1657-1662; Cantos, F.J., Tellería, J.L., Stopover site fidelity of four migrant warblers in the Iberian Peninsula (1994) Journal of Avian Biology, 25, pp. 131-134; Coppack, T., Both, C., Predicting life-cycle adaptation of migratory birds to global climate change (2002) Ardea, 90 (3), pp. 369-377. , Spec. I; Coppack, T., Pulido, F., Berthold, P., Photoperiodic response to early hatching in a migratory bird species (2001) Oecologia, 128, pp. 181-186; Gatter, W., Zugzeiten und Zugmuster im Herbst: Einfluß des Treibhauseffekts auf den Vogelzug? (1992) Journal für Ornithologie, 133, pp. 427-436; Gyurácz, J., Csörgo, T., Differences between adults and juveniles in autumn migration in three warbler (Acrocephalus spp.) species. III. Hungarian Ornithological Association, Scientific session (1991) Szombathely, pp. 164-171; Hanla, Y., Tiainen, J., Vepsalainen, K., Delayed autumn migration as an adaptive strategy